On this anniversary in 1306, after midnight they went out os their shops and danced in the High Street opposite the Drapery. And as they were thus disporting themselves, came upon them Gilbert de Foxley with a naked sword in his hand, and would have broken up the dance Some ol them that knew him, came and wished to lead him away, beseeching him to do no hurt to any one, but he, breaking away from them, would have cut off the hand of William de Claydon‚ as he went in the dance.
